Abstract: High-dimensional survival analysis has emerged as a pivotal tool in precision medicine, offering insights into complex datasets characterized by numerous variables. This study explores advanced methodologies and applications of survival analysis in high-dimensional settings, emphasizing the integration of data science and machine learning techniques. Feature screening methods are highlighted for their ability to manage dimensionality, enhancing model interpretability and predictive accuracy. The application of artificial neural networks is discussed, showcasing their potential to capture intricate patterns within survival data. Furthermore, the study delves into statistical inference approaches that ensure robust and reliable conclusions. By leveraging these innovative techniques, the research aims to improve patient-specific predictions and treatment strategies, ultimately advancing the field of precision medicine. The findings underscore the importance of interdisciplinary approaches, combining statistical rigor with computational advancements, to address the challenges posed by high-dimensional survival data.
